    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Funerary custom from Spain and Latin America honoring deceased children. The children's bodies are usually decorated with flowers, dressed up in fine clothes; occasionally paper wings are attached to the body to resemble angel wings.</Note_Text>
